						<div class="postbody">lda MetaspriteX<br /><div class="quotetitle">bazz wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Nah man, haven't we helped enough? We have jobs you know</div><br />Do you not have Christmas break?<br /><br />Anyway, I tried to make it myself and I had tried to use an incrementing pointer for it, but I couldn't figure out how to get it to work. This just codes for a simple 32x16 sprite. I made it so &quot;MetaspriteX&quot; and &quot;MetaspriteY&quot; make the sprite move.<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp; &nbsp;ldy MetaspriteY<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sta SpriteBuf1+0<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sty SpriteBuf1+1<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;lda #$00<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sta SpriteBuf1+2<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;lda #$30<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sta SpriteBuf1+3<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;lda MetaspriteX<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;adc #$10<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sta SpriteBuf1+4<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sty SpriteBuf1+5<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;lda #$00<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sta SpriteBuf1+6<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;lda #$30&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sta SpriteBuf1+7</div><br />I know this can be made way better somehow because it looks terribly inefficient.</div>

